      "body": "From @bwesterb:\r\n\r\n> Under memory you could mention that memory (and code size) are a huge deal for (the lower end of) embedded platforms. A yubikey, for instance, only has a few kilobytes of RAM. And, for custom hardware, RAM is typically more expensive than recomputing some stuff.\r\n\r\n",
